## Memory Instructions
- At the START of every session, call the memory tool to search for context about this project
- Search for: project structure, recent decisions, file patterns, known issues
- After completing any significant task, save key decisions and patterns to memory
- Before reading a file you've read in a previous session, check memory first
- Save to memory: important file locations, architectural decisions, naming conventions, Redux slice patterns, Turborepo workspace layout

## Project Stack
- Monorepo with Turborepo (check turbo.json for workspace config)
- Apps in /apps, shared packages in /packages
- React + Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Redux
- Custom MCP tools are available - check what tools are connected before starting tasks

## Token Saving Rules
- Do not read a file unless it is directly needed for the current task
- Do not explore directory trees unless asked
- Use memory context instead of re-reading files already seen this session
- Prefer targeted reads (specific line ranges) over reading entire files
